Vox raids!</span><hr size=1> You really should include a name in a post like this. Otherwise, it's pretty much a wasted exercise. Anyone who was on a raid like this would know who lead the raid, so presumably they wouldn't need your post as a warning. Others have no idea who you are talking about, and might try guessing who it is. This could affect the reputation of other bards around level 50. Suppose a different bard decided to host a raid this week. You think anyone is going to go along? If I got a tell from a bard asking to join a raid I'd say no way thinking it's this guy. <br><br>Suden Deyth <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uonimuro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Onimuro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/30/02 7:38:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: BEWARE the Vox raids!</span><hr size=1> Sanon, he ruined a naggy raid to... <p><iMG SRC = "http://lordofcheese.freeservers.com/images/OnimuroSig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uthenanin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Nanin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/7/02 3:42:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re</span><hr size=1> Just thought I'd in my own 2 cp about this , but this guy seems to be making a name of himself ... once I just read the title of this thread , knew it was Sanon ... I've known of 3 raids he's done , and all 3 failed , 2 with almost complete wipe-outs that took 2 hours to do CR's on , and other a complete wipe-out , unknown time of CR's .  <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/umergancyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mergancyr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/02 10:19:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   HEY, now</span><hr size=1> I dunno this guy Sanon or whatever, but who can say that they ruled all of their raids I give him hats off for trying, maybe he's a true MAIN, you all remember that right?  <br><br>At least this bard is trying to learn how it goes, now I havent been on any raids of his, so I shouldnt' comment maybe, but c'mon, are you really gonna dog ONE person because of a failed raid, I mean there are a LOT of people on raids, and they can put imput. I'm sure if this fellow was as incompetent as you say he got a lot of imput.<br><br>Point is, try and put yourself in someone elses shoes before you trash em, I mean he might not even know the dungeon layoutt, or anything, is that bad? maybe, but guess what, a lot of uber guilds hold their class officers responsible for raids even if they dont know the dungeon.<br><br>I suggest you try and help this person instead of flaming them. Thanks for your time<br><br>Merg<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uglasya7.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Glasya7</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vending Machine</span><br>  Posts: 259<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/02 10:45:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HEY, now</span><hr size=1> If he doesn't know what he is doing or even dungeon layout or MOB info he has no place running a raid.  He should go along a few successful ones and learn how to do it, then run his own.  Incompetence is not an excuse.<br><br>Sounds like he had no clue what he was doing and led many people to die.  Nothing is worse than a n00b running a pickup raid...<br><br> <p><table><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom" style=""><a  href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=84260" target="_magelo_" style="text-decoration: none;"><font style="font-family: Arial Black; font-size: 16px; color: red;"><b>Glasya</b></font></a></td><td><big><a href="http://www.foreverquest.com/" style="text-decoration: none;"><font style="font-family: Arial Narrow; font-size: 16px; color: rgb(255,0,0);">&lt;Fires Within&gt;</font></a></big></td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uulman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ulman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/8/02 10:55:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.i-mockery.com/minimocks/boxes/stormshadow-box.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HEY, now</span><hr size=1> I tend to agree with Glaysa here. Leading a raid such as a Naggy or Vox isn't like a pick up group. It requires planning, preperation and execution.<br><br>If you just charge blindly in, you aren't going to win, even if with lots of people. If you do not do some research ahead of time and plan accordingly, you just aren't going to win.<br><br>Naggy/Vox aren't hard mobs if you are properly prepared. Also, these mobs are not new mobs or challenges like Seru or the Snake Emporer. These mobs have been around for many years and thier tactics are well known. There is even more than one tactic.<br><br>Bottom line is, this is the risk we take if we choose a pick up raid. Just the thought of &quot;pick up&quot; raid gives me the shivers. I've been on my share of these types. Some we managed to scrape by, others were just terrible. Imaging getting a &quot;pick up&quot; baseball team to play the New York Yankees (or your favorite team <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). Chances are, more than likely, you aren't gonna win. hehe Same logic can be applied. You don't know the skills of your players, how well the coach is (if he even is a coach) and so forth. <br><br>anyhow, just my 2 cents. I don't know said person this is about, but maybe he should follow a few successful raids and learn a few tips and tricks. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://www.i-mockery.com/cards/images/card5-small.jpg"><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3771">Baron Thalzaar Zhiad'ra 60th Warlord</a> <BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3809">Ulman Moonspell 55th Conjurer </a><BR><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=3810">Chervik Mirroredsoul 47th Monk </a><BR>Guildleader of  <a target="new" href="http://www.geocities.com/eqconvergence">Convergence </a><BR><img src="http://www.ultimatemetal.com/forum/images/smilies/headbob.gif"> RAWK! <img src="http://www.ultimatemetal.com/forum/images/smilies/headbob.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub43.ezboard.com/uranmadar01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ranmadar01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/10/02 6:35:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: HEY, now</span><hr size=1> If he was truly 'trying to learn how it goes' he'd read one or two of the twenty or so 'Killing Vox/Naggy' guides that you can find on the net.  Just do a google search for 'Lady vox strategy.' <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=63.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=63.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.threadControl?topicID=63.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/space/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub43.ezboard.com/f7thhammerfrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=63.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub43.e